  "synonyms": [],
  "remark": "First (numeric) character is always 1 (see AAE038-005). Second (alphabetic) character indicates tolerance on temperature coefficient of capacitance: | sub-class code.................A......................B......................F......................C......................D | temp. coeff. ......................tolerance* ......tolerance*......tolerance*| +100 to -220....................+/-15.................+/- 30| -330 to -470.....................+/-30.................+/- 60| -750 to -1000...................+/-60.................+/-120.............+/- 250| -1500....................................................................................+/- 250| -2200 to -3300....................................................................+/- 500| -4700....................................................................................+/-1000| -5600....................................................................................+/-1000| +140 > TC > -1000.......................................................................................C| +250 > TC > -1750................................................................................................................D| tolerance* : tolerance on temperature coefficient in 10**-6}/K, |For the meaning of the values, see table II of IEC 60384-8 (1979).",
